Please answer each of the following questions in your own words; there is no right
or wrong answer, this questionnaire is designed only to get a sense of your
familiarity with certain tools and systems.


1. What are the benefits of infrastructure as code? How does this apply to the
modern data stack?


2. Describe 3 different methods for achieving parallelism in Python. What caveats or
considerations should a developer be aware of with each?


3. A data engineer has a collection of common Python functions that they would
like to share with their team in a version controlled way - what tools and patterns
would you recommend?


4. Both Prefect and Kubernetes are orchestration tools; what similarities and
differences do they have along this dimension?